    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1656"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1656">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2325.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Clare</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 7, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department informed that barracks at Bluefields were attacked July 5 by party
                    headed by Clifford D. Sands, who, it is reported, has taken refuge in your
                    Consulate. If careful investigation convinces you that report of attack is true,
                    Sands should not be sheltered in Consulate. Report by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
